features: ['Military-Inspired Black Dial with Full Arabic Numerals & 24-Hour Time', 'Green Nylon Strap', 'Durable and Lightweight Green Resin Case', 'Luminescent Hands', 'Case Lug Width: 19 mm', 'Water resistant to 30 m (99 ft): In general, withstands splashes or brief immersion in water, but not suitable for swimming']
description: ["You can tell a lot about a man by the watch he wears. This one is handsome and well-made. Plus it's a Timex, so you can feel good about it. The Timex Men's T41711 Camper Green Nylon Strap Watch features a black dial displaying white full Arabic numerals and 24-hour time. This watch is water resistant up to 30 meters (99 feet), so you can wear it when you swim, shower, or play water sports. The comfortable green nylon strap and light-weight resin case are crafted for durability. A reliable buckle ensures your watch remains on your wrist securely while partaking in outdoor activities.", 'Get ready to head to the great outdoors for a weekend of hiking or mountain biking with the Timex T41711 Camper watch. It has a medium-sized round, brown resin case that will be able to take a licking. It frames a black dial background with full Arabic numeral display, luminous dotted markers and hands (with seconds hand), and inset 24-hour marks. It also features a nylon grosgrain strap in olive, 10-year battery life, and water resistance to 30 meters (99 feet).', 'Casio', 'With the launch of its first watch in November 1974, Casio entered the wristwatch market at a time when the watch industry had just discovered digital technology. As a company with cutting-edge electronic technology developed for pocket calculators, Casio entered this field confident that it could develop timepieces that would lead the market.', 'Today, Casio is focusing its efforts on solar-powered radio-controlled watches: the built-in solar battery eliminates the nuisance of replacing batteries, atomic timekeeping means the users never have to reset the time. Recently, Casio launched a series of Bluetooth watches that sync to the users cell phone to automatically update the time. Casio is always moving time forward.', 'See more']

text: just beautiful
title: Bulova Women's 96T14 Crystal Watch
features: ['Made in USA or Imported', 'Due to a recent redesign by Bulova, recently manufactured Bulova watches, including all watches sold and shipped by Amazon, will not feature the Bulova tuning fork logo on the watch face.', 'Mineral crystal', 'Stainless-steel case; mother-of-pearl dial', 'Quality Japanese-quartz movement']
description: ['This Bulova dress watch is a dazzling accent in gleaming stainless steel and genuine Swarovski® crystals. The perfectly round polished steel case showcases a shimmering mother-of-pearl dial with petite Dauphine hands, a slender seconds hand, and silvertone dot markers. Sparkling round-cut crystals surround the dial and continue along the center link of the graceful steel bracelet, which features rounded and brightly polished outer links and a simple jewelry clasp. This Bulova watch offers precise Japanese quartz movement and is rated water resistant to 30 meters.', 'In 1875, a young Czech immigrant named Joseph Bulova set up shop in New York City, and a legendary American watch brand was born. Bulova was trained as a jeweler, and his expertise carried over into his watchmaking career, which began around 1911 with boudoir clocks and pocket watches, and soon evolved to include what was then one of the latest and most fashionable technological innovations: the wristwatch.', 'Bulova introduced its first line of wristwatches in 1919. The company grew and prospered, and soon early radio and television ads were declaring, "America runs on Bulova time." In the 1950s, continuing its legacy of innovation, Bulova introduced Accutron, the first electronic watch, and the first breakthrough in timekeeping technology in over 300 years. The Accutron timing mechanism was later adapted for use by NASA computers and a Bulova timer was even placed on the moon to control transmissions of data. Bulova timepieces have kept official time aboard Air Force One and have also served as official timepieces for U.S. Olympic teams.', 'Today, Bulova maintains its tradition of excellence in technology and design, offering a diverse collection of beautiful precision timepieces for every occasion.']

Gold-tone index beads embellish the face, and a handy digital display allows a dual-time capability or day-and-date calendar. The black resin band comes equipped with a durable buckle closure. Other details include a stationary, resin-and-stainless steel bezel and 30-millimeter resin case. Fusing technological details with a sleek design, this handsome timepiece tells everyone that you value style. text: Not a lot of wow factor here but you get what you pay for. Its just ok. i thought it would be a nice homage to the crescent city.
title: Amazon Collection 14k Yellow Gold Moon and Star Diamond Pendant Necklace, 18"
features: ['14k yellow gold necklace featuring white diamond moon and star pendnat', 'Rope chain with spring-ring clasp', 'Carat weight listed is the total for all stones.', 'All our diamond suppliers confirm that they comply with the Kimberley Process to ensure that their diamonds are conflict free', 'Great for everyday wear', 'Imported']
description: ['This dreamy moon and star pendant is fashioned from two-tone 14 karat gold and accented with genuine diamonds. The polished yellow gold crescent moon frames a five-point star set with ten petite round diamonds, for a total weight of .03 carat. The pendant is showcased on a yellow gold rope chain that fastens with a spring ring clasp. Youthful and charming, this pendant makes a fine gift that will remind her to reach for the stars.', 'The Amazon Curated Collection', 'Discover the Amazon Curated Collection of fine and fashion jewelry. The expansive selection of high-quality jewelry featured in the Amazon Curated Collection offers everyday values that range from precious gemstone and diamond pieces to the latest fashion designs.', 'This hand-selected assortment features an array of diamond, gemstone, and precious metal designs that receive a quality inspection, including from Amazon’s staff graduate gemologist, to ensure they meet Amazon’s high standards. All diamonds featured in the Amazon Curated Collection are certified by our suppliers to be conflict free, and IGI, GIA, or AGS certifications are provided on white diamonds of .75 carats or larger on all stud earrings, rings, and pendant necklaces.', 'Pieces from the Amazon Curated Collection come packaged in a custom box, making them wonderful gifts. In addition, we offer free one-day shipping within the continental U.S. on items over $500. International shipping options for friends and family overseas are available for an additional fee.', 'The Amazon Curated Collection offers a specialized customer service team that is available seven days a week to answer any product questions before, during or after the purchase. If you’re not satisfied for any reason, you will receive a full refund and free return shipping within the U.S. if you return your purchase within 30 days.', 'Find a special gift for a loved one or a beautiful piece that complements your personal style with jewelry from the Amazon Curated Collection.', 'Diamond Clarity:', "No two diamonds are alike. A diamond's most distinguishing characteristics are its inclusions, marks that are often invisible to the naked eye. However, under a jeweler's magnifying loupe or microscope they can look like crystals, tiny rivers, or clouds. A diamond's clarity is determined by the presence or absence of inclusions--fewer inclusions mean better clarity--and how visible they are. The greater a diamond's clarity, the greater its brilliance and value. A diamond categorized as internally flawless will have no inclusions, but this is extremely rare.", 'Diamond Color:', 'Though diamonds come in a wide range of colors, colorless diamonds have traditionally been considered the most valuable. Most diamonds are graded on a scale using the letters of the alphabet, from D (colorless), the best grade, through Z (a light yellow). It is difficult for the untrained eye to notice such variations in color unless stones are being compared side by side.', 'Diamond Carat Weight:', "A diamond's weight is measured in carats, with one carat being equivalent to 100 points. You will often see a diamond referred to as a 3/4-carat stone or a 75-point diamond. Larger stones are often more highly valued, but size should not be the only consideration--high brilliance, which varies according to clarity, cut, and color grade, is highly desirable in a diamond.", 'Diamond Certification:', 'A diamond certificate represents independent verification that the stone purchased has all the qualities of cut, color, clarity, shape, and weight expected. It is a further indication of the condition and value of that diamond as represented on our site. Such certificates are issued by several agencies employing highly trained gemologists and provide an unbiased and accurate evaluation of the diamond. These gemologists scrutinize each stone to analyze its dimensions, clarity, cut, color, finish, symmetry, and other details.', 'Diamonds purchased from the Amazon.com Collection may be certified by the Gemological Institute of America or the International Gemological Institute. The type of certificate provided will be noted in the product specifications of your jewelry purchase; if you do not see a certificate type noted, one will not be provided.', 'Our Diamond Policy:', "Amazon.com sources high-quality diamonds from some of the world's largest suppliers. All our diamond suppliers certify that to their best knowledge their diamonds are not conflict diamonds.", 'Diamond Care:', 'Diamonds, as the hardest substance on earth, are resistant to damage. However, diamond jewelry is set in different metals, and care will vary from piece to piece. Diamonds should be cleaned in a solution of one part ammonia to six parts water, using a gentle scrubbing brush to remove any dirt. It is a good idea to have them cleaned once a year by a professional jeweler, at which time the security of the setting can be checked as well. Diamond jewelry should be stored in a soft cloth pouch to ensure that the stone will not scratch other jewelry.', 'Gold Purity', "The purity of gold is measured in karats. Pure gold measures 24 karats but is too soft in this state to be used effectively in jewelry. So it is alloyed with other metals--silver, copper, nickel, and zinc--to increase its strength and durability. Common measurements once the alloy is added are 18 karat (75% gold), 14 karat (58%), and 10 karat (47.7%). In the United States, the legal karat limit for the metal to still be considered gold is 10 karats. A higher karat measurement in gold content indicates a greater value of the jewelry piece. Gold jewelry should always be stamped with the karat mark, either 18k, 750 (European marking for 18k), 14k, 585 (European marking for 14k), or 10k. In addition, to assure its quality, the piece should be stamped with the manufacturer's trademark or country of origin.", 'Gold Color', 'The color of gold may vary based off of the type of metal alloy included and the percentage of the metal alloy used. Most commonly, gold is available in yellow, white, and rose coloring.', 'Yellow gold is the most common color and is usually alloyed with silver and copper. Yellow and white gold are similar in strength and malleability, making them perfect for jewelry that is worn daily.', 'White gold is alloyed with nickel, copper, and zinc--and while it looks similar to platinum, it has vastly different properties.', 'Rose-colored gold is alloyed with copper and is often used to accent white or yellow gold. The saturation of color varies from piece to piece and according to gold content.', 'Caring For Your Gold Jewelry', 'To keep gold shining and scratch-free, avoid contact with chlorine and other harsh chemicals. Do not wear jewelry during rough work and be sure to store it in a fabric-lined jewelry box or pouch. To clean gold jewelry, use warm water, a mild soap, and a soft bristled brush, if needed.']

title: Seiko Men's SGG711 Titanium Watch
features: ['Made in USA or Imported', 'Titanium watch featuring round black dial with day/date window, luminous hands, and Arabic hour markers', '37 mm titanium case with hardlex dial window', 'Japanese quartz movement with analog display', 'Features three-link bracelet with fold-over clasp and safety', 'Water resistant to 50 m (165 ft): In general, suitable for short periods of recreational swimming, but not diving or snorkeling.']
description: ["Titanium case with a titanium link bracelet. Fixed titanium bezel. Black dial with luminous hands and Arabic numeral hour markers. Minute markers around the outer rim. Luminescent hands and markers. Date and day display appears at the 3 o'clock position. Quartz movement. Scratch resistant Hardlex crystal. Push / pull crown. Solid case back. Case diameter: 37 mm. Case thickness: 8 mm. Hidden deployment clasp. Water resistant at 50 meters / 165 feet. Functions: hours, minutes, seconds, day-date. AdditionalInfo: day/date display at 3 o'clock. Seiko Titanium Mens Watch SGG711.", "Elegance and precision make this Titanium Functional Watch from Seiko a perfect fit for any sophisticated man. Featuring a black dial with white Arabic numeral indices marking each hour, small white indices on the outer dial marking each minute, three trim hands, and a window displaying the day and date at three o'clock, this watch utilizes reliable Japanese quartz movement. Its 40.3-millimeter case, band with fold-over clasp, and stationary bezel are all crafted from strong, lightweight titanium for a luxurious look and feel. This watch offers the durability of a hardlex crystal, is water resistant to 165 feet.", 'From Humble beginnings, Kintaro Hattori\x92s Vision for Seiko has become reality. A consuming passion for excellence - imprinted in our Corporate DNA passed from generation to generation. Seiko, for 125 years committed to the art and science of time.', 'A culture of innovation connects a 19th century Tokyo clock shop with 20th century advances in timekeeping to an extraordinary 21st century "quiet revolution." Continually driven by dedication and passion, established a multitude of world\x92s first technologies\x85 transforming the principles of timekeeping.', 'The first quartz wristwatch \x96 changed the history of time.', 'The first Kinetic \x96 marked a new era in quartz watch technology.', 'In 1969, Seiko Astron, the first quartz wristwatch - was introduced.', 'In an instant, Seiko exponentially improved the accuracy of wristwatches \x96And Seiko technology firmly established today\x92s standard in Olympic and sports timing.', '1984, another celebrated first \x96 Kinetic Technology \x96 powered by body movement.', 'Kinetic \x96 a quartz mechanism with unparalleled accuracy \x96the driving force behind more world\x92s firsts.', 'Kinetic Chronograph \x96 the next generation of high performance timekeeping.', 'Kinetic Auto Relay \x96 automatically resets to the correct time.', 'Kinetic Perpetual - combining the date perfect technology of perpetual calendar with the genius of Kinetic Auto Relay.', 'And now Kinetic Direct Drive \x96 move, and the watch is powered automatically. title: Muck Boot unisex-adult Garden Shoes
features: ['100% Synthetic and fabric', 'Imported', 'Rubber sole', 'Lightweight garden shoe with waterproof natural-rubber upper featuring self-cleaning multiple-ribbed outsole', 'Pull tab at heel. clean up easily with a spray of water or gentle scrubbing with soap and water']
description: ['Lightweight and versatile, this rain shoe is perfect in the garden or around town.', "Keep your feet comfortable while tackling light gardening projects with the MuckBoots Adult Daily Shoe. These 100-percent waterproof, shoes have a stylish, sleek, streamlined design that's versatile enough to wear as a casual daytime shoe, but they're designed especially with outdoor work in mind. They feature durable, natural rubber uppers; an insulated shell that will keep your feet warm and dry in the winter as well as cool and comfortable in the warmer months; an extra-comfortable, lined footbed with moisture-control lining; and an easy-to-clean, dirt-resistant exterior. The unisex shoe is perfect for gardening, farm work, walking on the beach or playing at the park.", 'The story began in 1999 with the sole purpose of building the most comfortable, high performance footwear on the market. The need for a more comfortable boot for use in messy and tough conditions led to the design of The Original Muck Boot Company brand footwear. Every boot in the line is expected to deliver the same 100% waterproof quality and comfort that inspired the original footwear. In just a few years, the line has grown to more than 20 styles, all designed to tackle tough conditions in agriculture, lawn and garden, outdoor sporting, equine, and pet care. Today, the Muck Boot brand defines a standard of comfort and quality that goes beyond the expectations of customers around the country.', 'See more']

text:
I really like this watch because of its elegant design. However, it could probably just be that the one I got is defective, but it keeps resetting itself at least once a week!! Since it's both analogic and digital, you have to adjust it twice (three times actually since you can set up two different time zones for the digital one!). It's been a nightmare because I can't rely on it to keep me updated when I'm in a rush or so. Other than that, it looks awesome and it's discrete and beautifully designed.

** UPDATED REVIEW**
I just can't take it anymore! This watch is the worst! I end up setting up everything again once a day: what a nightmare! I am just going to give up. I wish Amazon and/or Casio would give me a refund. What a waste of money! I'm pretty sure it's not an old battery issue because it keeps working all day long, but all of a sudden, it resets itself and then keeps working again. I have always bought casio watches, but now I'm starting to think of probably not buying a casio again. It shouldn't be this way!
title: Casio Men's AQ47-1E Classic Ana-Digi Watch
features: ['Imported', 'Sporty watch featuring combo analog/digital display, 1/100-second stopwatch, and silver-tone pushers', 'Also features dual time, daily alarm, hourly time signal, and 12//24-hour formats', '29 mm stainless steel case with mineral dial window', 'Quartz movement with analog/digital displays', 'Polyurethane band with buckle closure', 'Water resistant to 30 m (99 ft): In general, withstands splashes or brief immersion in water, but not suitable for swimming']
description: ['The timeless style of an analog watch, combined with the functionality of a digital watch. This ana-digi combination allows you to see up to 2 times or the date with day of the week. For work or play, you’ll never lose track of time. Casual Classic Watch with a Black Face and a Resin Band.', "This sleek and sophisticated casual watch from Casio's Classic series is a stylish analog watch with convenient digital functions for the best of both worlds. The square black dial features gold-toned hands and dash indexes, while the amber-toned digital window below conveniently displays a second time or calendar date. The rectangular case is made of stainless steel, and the bezel and watch band are made of a rugged, dark gray polyurethane resin for a futuristic appeal. The analog quartz watch also offers a daily alarm, hourly time signals, and 1/100 second stopwatch capabilities. The timepiece is water resistance up to 99 feet.", 'Casio', 'With the launch of its first watch in November 1974, Casio entered the wristwatch market at a time when the watch industry had just discovered digital technology. As a company with cutting-edge electronic technology developed for pocket calculators, Casio entered this field confident that it could develop timepieces that would lead the market.', 'Today, Casio is focusing its efforts on solar-powered radio-controlled watches: the built-in solar battery eliminates the nuisance of replacing batteries, atomic timekeeping means the users never have to reset the time. Recently, Casio launched a series of Bluetooth watches that sync to the users cell phone to automatically update the time. Casio is always moving time forward.', 'See more']

text: Great product, great price. This is my 4th Casio Alarm Chrono. The watch keeps going but the plastic band breaks after about a year of use!! The low price makes the watch expendable, though, so I buy a new one every year or so. Thin profile, very comfortable on the wrist, and both analog and digital clock face.

text: Purchased this to carry a few items to the gym (towel, headphones, jacket, etc.) The bag is a nice size-not too small. Zip pocket on the outside is great to have. However, the fabric is very thin and stretches when anything heavy (e.g. a 18 oz water bottle) is carried. The bag is not finished very well. I have washed/air dried once and there is a lot of fraying on the inside. This bag is probably good for carrying very light but bulky items. The strings are awkwardly long when the bag is cinched closed. I'll probably cut to shorten them if I continue to use it.

description: ["In 1958, Hush Puppies created the world's first casual shoe, signaling the beginning of today's relaxed style. By utilizing supple pigskin suede, in combination with lightweight crepe soles, Hush Puppies created a soft, breathable and very comfortable shoe - an innovation that would ultimately change the kind of shoes we wear. In an era when footwear choices were limited, Hush Puppies provided the world with a new alternative. A modern shoe embraced for its authentic style and casual flair. Since the beginning, the beloved basset hound has embodied the easygoing nature that is Hush Puppies. Introduced during a time of new freedoms and changing lifestyles, the brand name and mascot quickly became symbolic of the emerging optimism of mid-century America. Relaxed and classic in design, Hush Puppies has always defined what it means to be modern and casual. Today, Hush Puppies continues to innovate, bringing technical excellence and genuine style to more than 130 countries."]

title: Dansko Women's Sonja Mule
features: ['100% Leather', 'Polyurethane sole', 'Platform measures approximately 1/2"', 'Leather and or fabric uppers', 'Padded instep collar for comfort when walking', 'Roomy reinforced toe box for protection with plenty of "wiggle room" for your toes', 'PU outsole with rocker bottom to propel foot forward and provide shock absorption', 'Wide heel strike for greater stability']
description: ["If you spend long hours on your feet, you have to pick up a pair from Dansko's Stapled Clog collection. Each has a polyurethane rocker-bottom sole, designed to protect the feet, legs, and back from the stress of standing or walking, and to propel the foot forward, helping you stay on the move.", "Ahhhhh, Dansko. There you go again. Doing your all-day comfort thing. Making us feel so good on our feet. With excellent arch support and legendary comfort, you let us stand longer than ever. And with great styles in a range of heel heights, you have us feeling all tingly inside, just like the day we first met. When wife and husband team, Mandy Cabot and Peter Kjellerup discovered the world's most comfortable shoe in a tiny shop in Denmark in 1990, they just had to bring some home for their friends. When their friends tried them on, they told their friends. And just like that, a shoe company was born. Now Dansko not only sells their original clogs, but also heels, boots, sandals, wedges and flats too! Every style features the Dansko DNA - materials and construction carefully selected to promote good foot, leg and back health, so that you can stand better, for longer. Say goodbye to choosing between looking good and feeling good. And say hello to having it all."]

description: ["The Casio Women's Digital White Resin Strap Watch #LW200-7AV combines the sporty style and functionality of a digital watch with the dependability of a 10-year battery. Recently, Casio launched a series of Bluetooth watches that sync to the users cell phone to automatically update the time. Casio is always moving time forward.']

text:
I'm seeing all these glowing reviews and thought it was worth a quick note to warn people: I badly wanted one of these jackets- as they tend to be pretty expensive, I bought a used one. When I got it I was totally happy with fit (I'm 5'7, 150, got L, like my jackets roomy) like the cut, the warmth, etc. I was horrified at the "phur" fabric. I don't know what all the person who had it first did, but it was all coarse and had balled up/matted up.

I do not know if it's a laundering issue or just how this material ages, but I was expecting 'soft.'

I ended up buying a (new) TNF Osito 2, and have been extremely happy.

text:
I recently received my new Seiko Solar Dive Watch. I didn't purchase this to wear diving as like most divers I use a computer and in fact have an air integrated Suunto Cobra computer on my HP Hose but I may still wear this as a back up timer. I will use this as a daily watch due to the robust build quality and waterproof design as I tend to go swimming a lot in the surf or sea kayaking. The watch is the same size as my Luminox but about twice the weight however the solar battery means no more battery changes every two years. I found the band a little narrow but have ordered a replacement. It's not uncomfortable for me and it seems about the right length to allow it to be worn over a thin wetsuit. The orange face is quite bright and very clear to read as are the day and date.

Pro's: Good size, not too small or large for an adult male
Clear bright watch face
No battery change required in the future
Waterproof to 200 meters
Comfortable watch band although stiff whilst new
Great value for the price

Con's: Heavy compared to a composite Luminox watch
Not as luminescent as a luminox (nothing else is that I have seen)
Would prefer if the band was a little wider
title: Seiko Men's SNE109 Stainless Steel Solar Dive Watch
features: ['Made in USA', 'Diver, Powered by light energy , 10-month power reserve once fully charged', 'Day/Date calendar , Screwdown crown and caseback', 'One way rotating elapsed timing bezel', 'LumiBrite hands and markers , 200M water resistant , Caliber V158', 'Pressure vented polyurethane strap']
description: ['Stainless steel case measures 42mm diameter by 10mm thick.', 'Stainless steel case measures 42mm diameter by 10mm thick.', 'Black genuine leather strap includes a stainless steel buckle.', 'Black genuine leather strap includes a stainless steel buckle.', 'Simple orange dial has contrasting luminous hands and hour markers.', 'Simple orange dial has contrasting luminous hands and hour markers.', 'Day and date display at the third hour.', 'Day and date display at the third hour.', 'The scratch resistant mineral crystal protects the water resistant to 200 meters case.', 'The scratch resistant mineral crystal protects the water resistant to 200 meters case.', 'Unique solar powered Quartz movement collecting any available light to store power.', 'Unique solar powered Quartz movement collecting any available light to store power.', 'From Humble beginnings, Kintaro Hattori’s Vision for Seiko has become reality. A consuming passion for excellence - imprinted in our Corporate DNA passed from generation to generation. Seiko, for 125 years committed to the art and science of time.', 'A culture of innovation connects a 19th century Tokyo clock shop with 20th century advances in timekeeping to an extraordinary 21st century "quiet revolution." Continually driven by dedication and passion, established a multitude of world’s first technologies… transforming the principles of timekeeping.', 'The first quartz wristwatch – changed the history of time.', 'The first Kinetic – marked a new era in quartz watch technology.', 'In 1969, Seiko Astron, the first quartz wristwatch - was introduced.', 'In an instant, Seiko exponentially improved the accuracy of wristwatches –And Seiko technology firmly established today’s standard in Olympic and sports timing.', '1984, another celebrated first – Kinetic Technology – powered by body movement.', 'Kinetic – a quartz mechanism with unparalleled accuracy –the driving force behind more world’s firsts.', 'Kinetic Chronograph – the next generation of high performance timekeeping.', 'Kinetic Auto Relay – automatically resets to the correct time.', 'Kinetic Perpetual - combining the date perfect technology of perpetual calendar with the genius of Kinetic Auto Relay.', 'And now Kinetic Direct Drive – move, and the watch is powered automatically. Or hand wind it and see the power you are generating in real time.', 'In the realm of fine watches, time is measured by Seiko innovation – A heritage of dedication to the art and science of time.']

Their innovative design includes a multi-layered, curved sole which makes for a unique and rewarding walking experience. The key to MBT is its patented sole structure. The shank, PU midsole with Pivot and the Masai Sensor create a soft surface that is akin to walking barefoot on springy moss or on a sandy beach. This creates a natural instability underfoot, which activates the supporting muscle system and has positive effects on the entire body. Wearing MBTs significantly improves your gait and posture and relieves pressure on your joints and back. It also exercises a large number of muscles, whether you’re walking or standing. This, in turn, stimulates your metabolism, burns extra calories and speeds up muscle regeneration. In addition, MBTs can have a firming effect on abdominal, leg and buttock muscles. Wearing MBT shoes can also be a therapeutic tool for back, hip, leg and foot problems. At MBT they don\'t believe in shoes. They believe in footwear that makes you better from the ground up.']

text: Bought these because I loved the look and they seemed to be excellent quality. I have two pair of Olukai which I love but have worn out after 2 years of constant use. I thought I'd splurge a little on these. After 2 days of wear I developed blisters on the tops of my feet and soreness between my toes. The material between the toes is thick hard leather. It is caused my toes to be very sore. The leather on the top of my feet ended up cutting into my skin to the point of bleeding. I wear flip flops ever day in the summer so my feet are no stranger to them. I was really disappointed that these didn't work out. It's unlikely I can return them because I wore them so will have to take the loss. I still think the construction is fantastic and the design is cool. I was told they'd break in but I'm not willing to suffer while they do.

With excellent arch support and legendary comfort, you let us stand longer than ever. And with great styles in a range of heel heights, you have us feeling all tingly inside, just like the day we first met. When wife and husband team, Mandy Cabot and Peter Kjellerup discovered the world's most comfortable shoe in a tiny shop in Denmark in 1990, they just had to bring some home for their friends. When their friends tried them on, they told their friends. And just like that, a shoe company was born. Now Dansko not only sells their original clogs, but also heels, boots, sandals, wedges and flats too! Every style features the Dansko DNA - materials and construction carefully selected to promote good foot, leg and back health, so that you can stand better, for longer. Say goodbye to choosing between looking good and feeling good. And say hello to having it all."]

text:
This is the third time buying one.

The good: Love the size, and they look in your carry on. I originally bought one, liked it enough that I bought another one for my wife.

The bad: they are kind of cheaply made. It looks like at first view that the inner felt is sewn onto the out leather looking case. This is not do, a few months later the felt inner started to come off as it is only glued on. I use mine more than my wife so she gave me hers. Now after a few months that one as well has come apart. I’m only buying a third one as it’s the nicest looking one I have found and like the size, but they are getting expensive when you have to buy a replacement only after a few months.

text:
I bought this Timex a short while ago to replace one that is years old and still keeps remarkably accurate time. But the finish eventually wore off in places and it needed a new battery. I went for the T2n949. It looks good, and it's utilitarian. And, it has a great pedigree.
I buy watches mostly for their utility. For many, many years I have found Timex to be a true value for money spent. This new, inexpensive Timex looks nice - that's a bonus. It keeps time very well, I can tell time in the dark of the morning and - if it's anything like it's long line of predecessors, it'll wear like iron. That's why I buy em and love em.
title: Timex Men's T2N949 Elevated Classics Stainless Steel Dress Watch with Two-Tone Expansion Band
features: ["Round watch featuring grey sunray dial with date display at 3 o'clock, Arabic hour markers, and Indiglo nightlight", '36 mm stainless steel case with mineral dial window', 'Quartz movement with analog display', 'Silver-tone expansion band with gunmetal-tone center stripe', 'Water resistant to 30 m (99 ft): In general, withstands splashes or brief immersion in water, but not suitable for swimming']
description: ["Timex Men's T2N949 Elevated Classics Dress Stainless Steel Expansion Band Watch Product Description: This stylish men's Elevated Classics Dress watch from Timex features a polished gunmetal brass case with a matching steel bracelet. The grey dial sets the stage for light grey hands and Arabic numerals for easy time-telling. Case: Brass with polished gunmetal Caseback: Stainless steel snap-down Bezel: Polished gunmetal Dial: Grey Hands: Light grey Markers: Light grey full Arabic numerals Calendar: Date display at 3 o'clock Indiglo Night-Light Bracelet: Stainless steel expansion band with polished gunmetal finish Crystal: Acrylic Crown: Push/pull Movement: Quartz Water resistance: 3 ATM/30 meters/99 feet Case measurements: 35 mm wide x 10 mm thick Bracelet measurements: 18 mm wide x 7 inches long Box measurements: 2.5 inches wide x 3.5 inches long x 3 inches high Model: T2N949", "The Timex Men's T2N9499J Easy Reader Gun Metal Case with Grey Dial Watch is a great example of a cool, casual timepiece packed with style. Featuring a black analog dial, date display and a grey stainless steel band, this watch is a must-have for your collection.", "Timex Group B.V. is one of the best-known American watch companies. Timex's U.S. headquarters are located in Middlebury Connecticut and it has substantial operations in China, the Philippines and India and full scale sales companies in Canada, the UK, France and Mexico.", 'The company began in 1854 as Waterbury Clock in Connecticut\'s Naugatuck Valley, known during the nineteenth century as the "Switzerland of America." Sister company Waterbury Watch manufactured the first inexpensive mechanical pocket watch in 1880. During World War I, Waterbury began making wristwatches, which had only just become popular, and in 1933 it made history by creating the first Mickey Mouse clock under license from Walt Disney, with Mickey\'s hands pointing the time.', 'During World War II, Waterbury renamed itself U.S. Time Company. In 1950 the company introduced a wristwatch called the Timex. Over the next three decades, Timex was sold through a series of advertisements which emphasized its durability by putting the watch through "torture tests," such as falling over the Grand Coulee Dam or being strapped to the propeller of an outboard motor, with the slogan "It takes a licking and keeps on ticking." With the help of former Olympic broadcaster, spokesman John Cameron Swayze, sales took off. The company later became Timex Corporation, then Timex Group and, to date, has sold over one billion watches.', 'The company has remained very competitive and the Timex brand continues its dominance through present day. Its primary market remains the United States and Canada, although the Timex brand is sold worldwide due to its ability to capitalize on its strong brand image and reputation for quality.', 'One of the most successful and important features available on many Timex watches is the Indiglo backlight system. Indiglo is a brand name of Indiglo Corporation, solely owned by Timex for licensing purposes. Timex electroluminescent lamps, branded Indiglo, were introduced in 1992 in the Ironman watch line. They were an immediate success. The Indiglo lamp uniformly lights the surface of the Timex’s watch dials in a manner that makes the dial read very easily in many different light settings. In some newer watches the Indiglo backlight only lights up the numbers, rather than the entire LCD display, which is achieved by means of a specialized film that inverts the LCD transmissivity.', 'Today, Timex Group products are manufactured in the Far East and in Switzerland often based on technology that continues to be developed in the United States and in Germany. With a large and varied line of watches, Timex has the style for everyone. From the locker room to the board room, there is a great Timex style time-piece for you.', 'See more']

Remove the links on your own to achieve just the right size, while avoiding expensive costs for jewelry/watch repair. Instructions for Use: 1) Place your watch link remover on a flat surface with the pin side up. 2) Place your watch band flat and flush to the left hand side wall on the watch link remover. 3) Line up the link that you want removed with the pin. 4) Turn the handle so that the watch link remover pin pushes against and pushes out the pin in your watch link. 5) Turn the handle so that the watch pin remover retracts, and then remove the pin from your watch link. SE is committed to providing the customer with the best source for value possible on the market. You will enjoy the quality, function and usefulness of our SE JT63057 Watchband Link Pin Remover (3 PC.). IPR Rights Notice: Important: Avoid getting counterfeit items. description: ["Saucony is among the most respected names in running shoes. We offer a wide range of running and walking shoes, each with the Saucony trademark fit, feel and performance. From our studies have come many innovative Saucony concepts. Advanced technologies-like Grid, the first sole-based stability and cushioning system--provide an advantage to athletes of all types."]

text: I had seen a ring in Neiman Marcus and Nordstrom that looked like this one however the diamonds were real and it retailed for $695. I really liked the ring however was having difficulty justifying spending this kind of money on a ring. Then I saw this similar ring on Amazon and thought at this price I should get this one. It said free returns so why not give it a chance. I ordered this ring while it was out of stock and it finally came in this week. I was nervous about opening the package because I was already in love with the one I saw in the store at the higher price tag. First off the box it comes in was so nice that I got even more nervous thinking the box is really what I am paying for. Then when I opened the box and saw the ring I was so excited because it looked just like the one I had seen in the stores. I think this is my favorite purchase off of Amazon to date. Would highly recommend this as a gift.

text: I bought these for my husband and he loves them. He says they run a tad large but feels the difference is thin socks vs. thicker socks. It would make sense that you wouldn't wear the thinner socks with active hiking shoes like these. However, if there are others out there that wear think no-shows -  these may make the fit feel a little big. They are great shoes and very durable. He walks a lot everyday and hikes. He says these are perfect for his active job as well as his hiking/climbing adventures.

text: First off, the terry material is significantly thinner and coarser than one would expect from a robe at this price point.  Beyond that, though, the way this robe is designed is simply ludicrous.  The hood is cut so small that if you put it up, the robe gets pulled about 2 inches off your shoulders so all the pressure of the robe is right on the top of your head and it looks more like a ghost costume than a robe.  Also, the belt loops are placed so high that it ties essentially at the bottom of your rib cage and the belt itself should be a good 8-10 inches longer.  I couldn't have been much more disappointed by this disaster of a robe.

If you’re not satisfied for any reason, you will receive a full refund and free return shipping within the US if you return your purchase within 30 days.', 'Find a special gift for a loved one or a beautiful piece that complements your personal style with jewelry from the Amazon Curated Collection.', 'Sterling Silver History', 'Experts believe that silver alloy, used today as sterling silver, originated in continental Europe in the 12th century. Pure silver was found to be a soft and easily damageable material. When combined with other metals, most commonly cooper, it produced a tougher material that could be heavily relied on. Throughout the next few centuries, sterling silver was used as currency and for household items. It was often used as silverware and became the material used in a proper table setting between 1840 and 1940 throughout the United States and Europe. Because of this popularity, silver companies began to grow. During this craze, companies began to experiment using sterling silver compositions in jewelry, as it was a material that was easy to mold into intricate designs and gave a luxurious look with its metallic finish. Today, sterling silver is widely used in all kinds of jewelry styles and shines as beautifully as other precious metals, with the benefit of affordable pricing.', 'Sterling Silver Composition', "While pure silver can be combined with many different types of metals, sterling silver is created when combining pure silver with copper. Sterling silver jewelry can be composed with different amounts of copper but is most often seen with the .925 stamp, meaning that the composition is of 92.5 percent silver and 7.5 percent copper. This has been found to be a good combination for maintaining the silver's durability without harming its sparkle.", 'Caring for Your Sterling Silver Jewelry', 'Silver should not come into contact with harsh household chemicals such as bleach, ammonia, or chlorine. To avoid scratches, store silver in a lined jewelry box or pouch, as it is prone to tarnish as it naturally reacts with sulfur or hydrogen sulfide in the air. Cleaning and wearing silver jewelry regularly will prevent this and help maintain its shine. Immediately upon noticing any discoloration, use a gentle polish made specifically for removing tarnish.']

It is the founding principle of our flagship and the radical notion that still drives us today. By being true to our convictions, we will continue to turn the balance of power, and deliver true Swiss luxury to anyone who desires it. Let all those who possess our timepieces and pass through our doors witness the quality, value and care in every piece we create, and the spirit of never-ending possibilities in everything we do."', "These are the words that greet visitors and motivate team members inside the Invicta Watch Group's new worldwide headquarters. Emblazoned in stainless steel, it has been the Invicta message since Day One.", 'With each new timepiece, the company sends up a flare for those looking to be defined not by how much they spend, but how wisely they spend. With its strong collections, the gutsy Swiss brand is guaranteed to keep attracting followers.', 'It takes years of training and a great deal of pride to achieve glorious Swiss timepieces by hand. But it takes guts and the courage of your convictions to make those timepieces affordable for everyone who appreciates them.', 'At our Swiss workshops, we mix time-honored traditions with a little bit of horse sense every single day to produce the greatest values in the watch-making world.', 'Created in a blend of fashion and class, this Invicta timepiece exhibits a bold style that adds flare to your collection.']

text:
This jacket arrived in good time at my resort in Orlando, Florida. It was 80F or more the entire 8 days on vacation and all the while it rained on and off. And when the rain was on, it was POURING. This jacket worked perfectly. It's just long enough to keep your bum dry if you need to sit (and I did after walking all over Disneyworld). The only issue is that I wear glasses and a bill (or flap, whatever you call it) on the hood would have really helped keep them dry. Lastly, the jacket isn't insulated, but the material is good and such that if its hot already, like in Florida, it doesn't feel all that nice to wear long sleeves.

Overall, good jacket; I used it a lot and it still looks brand new. I have a feeling it will last many years.

text:
This jacket looks very cool. I ordered large because the jacket is fitted. The only problem is the zipper with two sliders. I had to figure out how to use it, so in case somebody else has the same problem, here is how:
When using the two-way movable open end zipper, just pull the top slider to kiss the bottom end slider located at the open end box. Insert the zipper pin from other side of zipper, pull the top slider and you will get the zipper zipped.
To unzip the zipper, just pull down the top slider to the bottom end and pull out the inserting pin from other side of zipper.

The bottom open end is supposed to give you room at waist length, so that you can sit comfortably while wearing the jacket.

I don't like it the zipper, so I just use the buttons on the flap of the zipper and that works fine.

text: This jacket was EXACTLY what I was looking for in a rain jacket. It's lightweight, but warm at the same time. I took the advice of many of the reviews and ordered a small instead of an x-small and I'm glad I did. It is fitted and hugs my body, but I can still wear a lightweight sweatshirt underneath if needed. The arms are a tad long for me, but I have short arms and I anticipated them being a bit long for me - I'm sure they are the perfect length for most people. I like that the jacket is bit longer in length and covers me up. I received the jacket yesterday and it was pouring rain all day. I wore it out to fun a few errands and it kept me dry and it dried quickly once I was inside.  The hood covers my head and is not too big like some rain jackets. I trust Columbia and knew I was going to get a quality jacket and I did.  I would highly recommend this jacket if someone wants a fitted rain jacket that looks great and keeps you dry.

text: This is my 2nd pair of Crave boots! I love them and may end up with a couple more colors. The Grey color is difficult to describe... maybe a grungy warm soft brown grey would be too long, but more accurate. The suede upper is a soft charcoal grey. I do like the color a lot, it's different and looks great with leggings and jeans. When I first put them on, I thought they were too small. They were laced differently than my last pair so I unlaced and re-laced them, which completely fixed the issue. After reading hundreds of Taos Crave reviews, I believe others have failed to do this. This particular pair (40) fits like a U.S. size 9. My others are also size 40 and are a bit larger, they fit more like a U.S. 9.5. I may need to re-lace. :)  I have a high arch and fairly wide feet. These boots are the most comfortable footwear I own, next to my trainers.

Their shoes and boots are created with four principles in mind: quality, durability, comfort, and craftsmanship. text:
These boots are pretty comfortable and stylish but they rip SO easily. I bought a pair a few years ago and they began to tear on the sides within a few months. Because I loved the fit and style of the boots so much though, I ordered the same exact pair again. I used these as gardening boots at my summer job working at a big garden and they ripped within a month. I’m not sure what I was thinking but I decided to order them again because they had served me well before they ripped and they’re pretty cheap and everything. I thought I would be more careful and they wouldn’t rip, but of course they ripped within a few weeks of wearing at the garden!!!!

So, I would say these are decent rain boots if you’re intending to wear them infrequently only when it rains. However, if you’re planning to wear them regularly, do not waste your money on them! The material is cheap and they WILL rip!!!!

The waterproof boot has a natural rubber construction, textile lining and will provide ultimate comfort and warmth throughout the autumn and winter seasons."]

text:
Shoes were great while they lasted. That being said they only lasted around 5 wears before the rubber split at the seam between sole and main part of the boot (not an ideal place for waterproof boots to break). I really wanted to love these boots too. Right out box the boots the thin inner lining was starting to peel away from the rubber at the top of my right boot (before even putting them on), however I was willing to forgive an issue like that since it didn't impact the integrity of the boot itself. That though should have altered me that there would be issues with the boot down the road.

To be fair, the boot itself has great tread, thick soles, and is easy to put on for an ankle boot (I've found some ankle boots are extremely narrow and almost impossible to put on). Before the rubber ruptured they did their job, but boy was their life far shorter than I expected. I know $30 boots aren't meant to last forever, but I'd at least expect them to make it until Spring.

The reason why I am giving these boots a 3 is because after only 2 months of owning these boots, both have cracked so badly on the sides that they no longer suit their purpose. If you only plan to wear these once in awhile, then you will love them. If you need something that will be worn several times a week, buyer beware. I defintely got plenty of use out of these boots over the course of two months, but April showers bring May flowers and  apparently wet feet too!

description: ['ASICS rebels against conventional design with its new GEL-Kinsei 6. The upgraded seamless upper construction supplies superior comfort with improved fit and durability. With updated FluidRide technology, the enduring cushion of the GEL-Kinsei 6 ensures a lightweight experience for every journey of your run.The use of seamless materials reduces the potential for irritation and friction caused by traditional stitches and seams', 'In 1949, Mr. Kihachiro Onitsuka began his athletic footwear company (Onitsuka Co., Ltd.) by manufacturing basketball shoes out of his living room in Kobe, Japan. He chose the name ASICS for his company in 1977, based on a famous Latin phrase "Anima Sana In Corpore Sano," which, when translated, expresses the ancient ideal of "A Sound Mind in a Sound Body." Taking the acronym of this phrase, ASICS was founded on the belief that the best way to create a healthy and happy lifestyle is to promote total health and fitness. Today, ASICS offers a full line of performance-driven athletic shoes and technical active sports apparel and accessories dedicated to bringing harmony to the body and soul.']

title: Little Griddle WA-01-N 40 MM GrillTimer Watch and Grill Timer for Measuring Grilling and Cooking Times for Steak, Fish, Burgers and More Sauce and Water Resistant Quartz Movement,Black
features: ['Patent-Pending unidirectional "Grill Bezel" times eight popular grill recipes right on the watch', 'Instruction manual details timing compatibility of Grill Bezel for dozens of other recipes', 'Handsome 40 mm Stainless Steel case features classic styling and combination brushed and polished surfaces', 'Durable Japan-made Seiko quartz movement with date calendar', 'Sauce Resistant to 3 Tablespoons (mustard, BBQ, gravy, etc. )']
description: ['Grill Timer by Little Griddle is the brand new wristwatch and recipe timer for people who love to cook outside and it is the world\'s first wristwatch designed specifically to time outdoor cooking. It uses a version of the "elapsed time" concept that was used to track below-surface time on the iconic diving watches made famous during the 1950s and 1960s. Grill Timer combines classic three-hand wristwatch styling with a unidirectional rotating "Grill Bezel" to time popular outdoor recipes. Here\'s how it works: Grill Timer\'s patent-pending Grill Bezel times recipes by rotating left to align the start of a recipe (the small silver dot before the recipe title) with the Grill Timer\'s minute hand. As the minute hand moves across the face of the watch, the recipe is timed and the bezel indicates when the food should be flipped and when it should be removed from the grill. The bezel contains a ratcheting mechanism that only allows it to rotate to the left, ensuring that the Grill Bezel never indicates more time remaining to the recipe than there really is. This "fail-safe" feature helps to reduce the chance of over-cooking food on the grill. The recipe timing on the Grill Timer Grill Bezel features a silver-to-red gradient that indicates degree-of-doneness and while grills and foods vary in respective heat outputs and thicknesses, Grill Timer provides a very good indication of when a specific piece of food has been cooked to completion.']

features: ['100% Polyester', 'Zipper closure', 'Machine Wash', 'VaporActive, powered by 37.5, technology rapidly evaporates and removes sweat so you can dry faster, stay cooler and go longer', 'Lightweight full-zip vest with loose-fit stand collar, targeted vents, water-repellent finish, UPF 50, zippered pockets and reflective details make it the ultimate in performance, style and safety', 'Permanent technology embedded at the fiber level is chemical free, controls odor and is engineered to never degrade or wash out', 'Durable, water-repellent finish keeps you dry without sacrificing breathability', 'Targeted back vents increase air flow and enhance the overall cooling effect of the VaporActive fabric']
description: ['Our high tech transitional layer. The Mission VaporActive Dynamo Running Vest adapts to all conditions. The durable, water-repellent finish keeps you dry without sacrificing breathability. Targeted back vents enhance airflow on this lightweight, full-zip vest. Reflective details help keep you visible in low light conditions. UPF 50. VaporActive, powered by patented 37.5 technology, attracts moisture at the vapor level and rapidly removes sweat, keeping you cool, dry and comfortable. Permanently embedded at the fiber level, the fast-drying technology never degrades or washes out. Fabric contains active particles that attract and trap odor-causing molecules, later releasing them in the wash. Machine wash cold with like colors. Only non-chlorine bleach when needed. Do not use softeners. Tumble dry low. Do not iron.']

text:
I bought this as my teaching bag: easily holds two small laptops, overstuffed gradebook, files, and even a dslr camera at times. This, in addition to a place for a water bottle (or coffee thermos) and plenty of pouches to drop my phone and keys to free up my hands.
I like that it zips on top so it prevents things from spilling out on my car floor at sudden stops. Also - sits nicely on the floor under my desk and doesn’t fall over (flat bottom).
Straps are durable and long enough to easily fit on my shoulder even when wearing a thick winter coat. The material is pretty water resistant and wipes off easily too.
I’ve gone through a lot of work bags over the years, looking for the one that works for me and this one has fit the bill nicely so far.
title: Pursetti Utility Tote with Pockets & Compartments-Perfect Nurse Tote Bag, Teacher Bag, Work Bags for Women & Craft Tote
features: ['Polyester', 'Mesh,Polyester lining', 'Zipper closure', 'Wipe with Damp Cloth', 'Carry Your Daily Essentials in One Tote Bag-Whether you are a teacher, nurse, working woman or a soccer mom, this will be your go-to utility tote bag to stay organized. title: Nike Basketball Shoe
features: ['The Nike Air Force 1 Low “Go the Extra Smile” is a fun colorway of the classic sneaker from the “Have a Nice Day” collection that was released in November 2021', 'A reminder that you should have fun wearing your sneakers, the “Go the Extra Smile” colorway is a play on the motivational phrase, and a colorway that features embroidered smiley faces with Swoosh logos for mouths on the heel', 'A white tumbled leather base is paired with a black leather Swoosh on the sides', 'Classic “Nike Air” and Swoosh branding is embroidered on the heel', 'Additional “Nike Air” and “Air Force 1” detailing is found on the tongue tag on the black mesh tongue']
description: ["The legend continues to live in the Nike Air Force 1 '07, a modern version of the iconic AF1, combining classic style and modern details. The low design offers optimum soil adhesion and a classic look. This version of the Nike Air Force 1 features rippled leather edges for a cleaner, slimmer line and more refined details. The leather and fabric upper features external layers positioned at strategic points for a lifetime durability and support. The perforated inserts favor the breathability to keep the foot always fresh and dry."]

Now, the pants. I just love all the little pockets. You have a ton of cargo area, but to the normal observer, they'd never notice. The pants have a bit of stretch to them that is nice as well.

text:
Pros: Comfortable, hybrid pants (casual/nice), flattering
Cons: Too short (or sizing inconsistent), wrinkle easily, no pockets

These are comfortable, great looking casual pants that almost pass for dress pants; they are somewhere in between. They'd be fine for running around town in a T-shirt and flats or going out to a decent restaurant with a nice blouse and heels -- if only they were long enough. I don't think they're dressy enough to wear with the blouse tucked in as the lack of button and closure gives away their "yoga pant" origins. Unlike yoga pants, they wrinkle easily and stay that way.

I am 5'6", normally wear size 4, and based on the manufacturer's chart, I ordered a medium. The fit is generous and flattering up top, but the pants are far too short -- hitting above my ankle if they are pulled up to the designed high-waist position and at the ankles if I push them down to my hip bones, which makes the top fit ridiculous. The crotch area hangs below making my legs look 3-inches shorter, and the material on the behind then sags. I think perhaps the sizing is not consistent because I've read reviews from people taller than I who got the same size and say the length is perfect -- reaching well below the ankle and touching the top of the foot. I'm sad because I would have like to wear them out, but they're comfy, so I've decided to keep them for around the house -- high-water style.

text:
I bought a large army green backpack. The canvis is about .075" thick, so really thick. The seams are very well stitched and the backpack is built tough and very durable.

The pack is all canvis, no leather. The canvis straps snap to the bag, (non magnetic snaps), with metal hardware, not stainless steel, but definitely strong metal.

BAG SIZE, I am 5' 10" and I weigh 235 lbs. You can see in the images how this fits me. The bag is well balanced and feels comfortable and ergonomic to the shape of my body. The bag can hold at least 42 lbs. Which is the most weight I had inside of it. It held up perfectly for 5.5 hours with that constant weight.

text: I will freely admit that prior to this purchase, I was not a "watch enthusiast." I decided to start wearing a watch as a way to keep my phone in my pocket, and didn't really have high expectations for $53. I did my research, however, and in my opinion this is the best chronograph you can buy for less than ~$250. I've worn it almost daily since it arrived on October 3rd and there is no visible wear to speak of. No chipping of the finish on the case, no issues with the stitching on the band, nothing. I have had to adjust the hands on the chornometer dials once, and that was after the first use. Again, you will not find a better daily-wear chono for the price, or even 5x the price, in my opinion. I would certainly purchase again.
title: Timex Men’s TW4B12300 Expedition Field Chronograph Tan/Black Leather Strap Watch

description: ["The Timex Expedition Field Chrono draws design inspiration from vintage military watches. The unique dial features numerals in increments of five up to 60 and three sub-dials that track minutes, seconds, and 1/20 of a second for up to 30 minutes. An easy to operate date window is located at 4 o'clock. With the Quick Date function, you can set the date on the watch without turning the crown for every 24-hour period. Just pull the stem halfway out, and turn until desired date is reached. It also offers water resistance to 330 feet (100 meters) and a durable leather strap. The Indigo night-light uniformly lights the surface of the watch dial using patented blue electroluminescent lighting technology. It uses less battery power than most other watch illumination systems, enabling your watch battery to last longer.", "The Timex Expedition Field Chrono draws design inspiration from vintage military watches. text: Not impressed. There was a lot of material in the front which was great for concealing a food baby, but the back hugged and had no additional material to allow the dress to flow (no pleating, etc.). In addition to not appreciating the way it looked on my back/rear, the combination between the slim fitting back and the very loose front looked odd to me.  The green is beautiful, the fabric is so fun, and the price is great. Unfortunately I wanted to look good all the way around so I returned it.

Easy to get him in and out of it.  My husband had purchased the blue one, and I knew getting a second one would be a great investment.  We got the 12-18 month size, which is a little big as my son is only 9m - so there is plenty of room for him to grow into in.  And it will last all winter for us.

text:
For reference, I'm 6' tall, at 170 lbs. This shirt hits my shoulders just right, but for the rest of it through, it fits rather loose. It's not loose to the point of being baggy or annoying, but just a bit looser than I usually wear my shirts. The colour is a nice pale yellow, but a saturated pale yellow, if that makes sense. It's not like if they just didn't dye the fabric with enough colour and that's why it's such a muted colour. It's more that they achieved a subtle colour, and really dyed the shirt properly. I can tell, because the colour has maintained itself through a few washings now.

The fabric is very light. This would be excellent summer wear, when you want something easy breezy that breathes well in a light colour. This ticks 100% of the boxes, and is stylish looking to boot!

text:
I have 19 piercings and after losing the ball to one of my hoops, decided to try ordering from amazon. I loved the idea of this item because of how many options I had. I figured, though I was buying for my tragus, I would have other rings for my cartilage piercings and others.

No. The ball is soooo tiny, I wouldn't be able to use these for ANYTHING. They wouldn't allow the skin to go through because of how tiny it was. I have already started the refund. Just extremely disappointed and feel that the product was mislabeled. There is no way this would fit a tragus.

text: I purchased this belt to wear with a lace gown.  I bought 2 of them so that the pearls would go all around the dress.  Otherwise, you would have the ribbon on the back. I will have the seamstress tack it to the dress so that it doesn't slip down.  The lace is heavy on the dress and I first purchased a belt  that had more rhinestones but I felt that it was too sparkly/heavy looking on the lace.  This looks perfect!  I love it and can't wait to wear it for my 50th wedding anniversary.

description: ['The (variant) cover that started it all. In December of 2002, writer Jeph Loeb and artist Jim Lee kicked off the legendary "HUSH" story arc. Yep, beginning in Batman #608 and running through issue #619, Batman dealt with the machinations of a strangely bandaged baddy who, along with The Riddler, ran the Caped Crusader through a rogue-riddled gauntlet. Our Batman Hush Cover Men\'s T-Shirt features the striking variant cover to Batman #608 -- this powerful work also covers the very first trade paperback collection. And yes, since legendary artist Jim Lee handled the dark, detailed interiors you better believe he crafted the criminal-ridden covers. Case in point, this EXCLUSIVE "HUSH"-themed Batman t-shirt is brimming with thick, clear lines, ominous sketches of string-pulling rogues, and a smoky Gothic tone that beseeches readers to enter with extreme caution. Oh! And don\'t miss that "HUSH" logo stamped on the left sleeve. NEAT!']

These socks are the right amount of thickness to be comfortable without any slippage at all, but still not thick enough for working out (for my taste anyway). Somehow the combo of the design and sticky pad on the back really helps with the slippage problem. Plus it's a way better deal than Bombas. To address some of the comments made from other reviewers - If you don't over pull them on, they don't bunch at the heel. I wore them all day and no fraying of material around toes at all. For reference, my shoe size is Women's 6 and I got a size Small.

text:
I wear a women’s 9.5 wide or extra wide shoe. I usually opt for extra wide. I was not sure what size to order so I decided with the larger 11-12 M, size because I purchased a 9 -10 size in a different slipper from a different store and it was a tad bit short. When I first got the slippers I was able to slide my foot in without having to wiggle it. They are a tiny bit too wide but that’s OK. They have not stretched much since I’ve been wearing them.

The slippers are very comfortable and I can get in and out of them very easily. One thing though, once I almost stepped out of them by accident when I was not careful. If you’re not sure what size to order, you can send them back for a different size. Or, order two sizes try on the smaller size first and return the one that doesn’t fit. I love these memory foam slippers a lot and would certainly buy them again!
